    "body": "### Problem\n\nBuild-in tree-sitter have trouble in parsing c code that contain macro that can't be recognized as a statement\nFor example,\n```c\n#define A 10\nint main(){\n  int a=A;\n}\n```\n`:InspectTree` will get error node, while\n```c\n#define A return 0\nint main(){\n  A;\n}\n```\nwill get good grammar tree.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- Run `nvim --clean foo.c`\n- Write\n```c\n#define FOO 10\nint main{int foo=FOO;}\n```\ninto that file\n- Run `:InspectTree`\n- You will get the wrong grammar tree, which is\n```\n(translation_unit ; [0, 0] - [2, 0]\n  (preproc_def ; [0, 0] - [1, 0]\n    name: (identifier) ; [0, 8] - [0, 11]\n    value: (preproc_arg ; [0, 12] - [0, 14]\n      (translation_unit ; [0, 12] - [0, 14]\n        (ERROR ; [0, 12] - [0, 14]\n          (number_literal))))) ; [0, 12] - [0, 14]\n  (function_definition ; [1, 0] - [1, 24]\n    type: (primitive_type) ; [1, 0] - [1, 3]\n    declarator: (function_declarator ; [1, 4] - [1, 10]\n      declarator: (identifier) ; [1, 4] - [1, 8]\n      parameters: (parameter_list)) ; [1, 8] - [1, 10]\n    body: (compound_statement ; [1, 10] - [1, 24]\n      (declaration ; [1, 11] - [1, 23]\n        type: (primitive_type) ; [1, 11] - [1, 14]\n        declarator: (init_declarator ; [1, 15] - [1, 22]\n          declarator: (identifier) ; [1, 15] - [1, 18]\n          value: (identifier)))))) ; [1, 19] - [1, 22]\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nGet the correct grammar tree, that is\n```\n(translation_unit [0, 0] - [2, 0]\n  (preproc_def [0, 0] - [1, 0]\n    name: (identifier [0, 8] - [0, 11])\n    value: (preproc_arg [0, 12] - [0, 14]))\n  (function_definition [1, 0] - [1, 24]\n    type: (primitive_type [1, 0] - [1, 3])\n    declarator: (function_declarator [1, 4] - [1, 10]\n      declarator: (identifier [1, 4] - [1, 8])\n      parameters: (parameter_list [1, 8] - [1, 10]))\n    body: (compound_statement [1, 10] - [1, 24]\n      (declaration [1, 11] - [1, 23]\n        type: (primitive_type [1, 11] - [1, 14])\n        declarator: (init_declarator [1, 15] - [1, 22]\n          declarator: (identifier [1, 15] - [1, 18])\n          value: (identifier [1, 19] - [1, 22]))))))\n```\nwhich is parsed by https://github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-c\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.2 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1748459687 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI do not know\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nGNU/Linux 6.15.6-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.42.1 created by Kovid Goyal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
